=== P-F Error Union + Retry Logic Probe ===

Test 1: SQLITE_BUSY (code=5) through union
  Mapped to: Common:Connection_error
  Attempt 1: retry with backoff
  Attempt 2: retry with backoff
  Attempt 3: retry with backoff
  Result: retry loop exhausted

Test 2: SQLITE_LOCKED (code=6) through union
  Mapped to: Common:Transaction_error
  Attempt 1: retry immediate
  Attempt 2: retry immediate
  Attempt 3: retry immediate
  Result: retry loop exhausted

Test 3: SQLITE_CONSTRAINT (code=19) through union
  Mapped to: Common:Constraint_violation
  Attempt 1: fail
  Result: fail immediately

Test 4: SQLITE_IOERR (code=10) through union
  Mapped to: Common:Io_error
  Attempt 1: retry with backoff
  Attempt 2: retry with backoff
  Attempt 3: retry with backoff
  Result: retry loop exhausted

Test 5: Unknown code (code=99) through union
  Mapped to: Sqlite variant
  Attempt 1: fail
  Result: fail immediately

=== Verdict ===
P-F: Error union + retry logic
  - BUSY (5) -> Connection_error -> Retry with backoff: preserved
  - LOCKED (6) -> Transaction_error -> Retry immediate: preserved
  - CONSTRAINT (19) -> Constraint_violation -> Fail: preserved
  - IOERR (10) -> Io_error -> Retry with backoff: preserved
  - Unknown -> Sqlite variant -> Fail: preserved

The union preserves retry-relevant categories.
BUSY vs LOCKED distinction is maintained via different Common variants.
